claim.claim-text:
8. A loudspeaker comprising:
a housing having a forepart widening towards a front side, a base part extending towards a rear side, and an intermediate part between the forepart and the base part, the intermediate part being connected to the forepart and the base part by transition areas;
a diaphragm flexibly connected to the housing; and
an actuator for displacing the diaphragm with respect to the housing;
wherein the transition areas behave as hinges under a load so that the intermediate part turns towards a central axis of the loudspeaker extending between the forepart and the base part, and wherein the intermediate part does not break under the influence of the load.
